<item>
            <title>[SPARK-35929] Schema inference of nested structs defaults to map</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-35929</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Inferring schema for struct columns&#160;causing schema issues as below.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
data = [{&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;inside_struct&quot;&lt;/span&gt;: {&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;payment&quot;&lt;/span&gt;: 100.5, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;name&quot;&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Lee&quot;&lt;/span&gt;}}]
df = spark.createDataFrame(data)
df.show()
+--------------------+
|       inside_struct|
+--------------------+
|{name -&amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;, pa...|
+--------------------+
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &quot;inside_struct&quot; is a map, and the &quot;name&quot; column inside of it becomes null.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The schema inferring might decide on a map type with a value type of the first field of the struct, we should fix it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
